<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-12-31T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1952-01-01T20:00:00-05:00" n="1095" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d1095">
                            <head><hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi></head>
                            <p>Acting Secretary of State <persName corresp="#p_HHCJ1">Hoover</persName> and the Indian Ambassador to the United
                                States, <persName corresp="#p_MGL1">G.L. Mehta</persName>, on
                                October 21, 1954, signed and thereby brought into force a United
                                States–India copyright agreement. For the text, see <gloss target="#t_TIAS1">TIAS</gloss> No. 3114, printed in 5 <gloss target="#t_UST1">UST</gloss> (pt. 3) 2525.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>